### 1. Create a Test User (Required for the cart)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password_hash": "dummy_hash"
}

### (If the above fails because the users API doesn't have a POST, you might need to create a user directly in Supabase or via a signup page)

---

### 2. Create a Test Product (Required to add an item to the cart)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Product",
  "price": 19.99
}

---

### 3. GET the Cart
# Replace `1` with the actual userId you got from step 1
GET http://localhost:3000/api/carts?userId=1

---

### 4. POST (Add item to Cart)
# Replace `userId` and `productId` with actual IDs from your database
POST http://localhost:3000/api/carts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 1,
  "productId": 1,
  "quantity": 2
}

---

### 5. PUT (Update Cart Item Quantity)
# Replace `cartItemId` with the ID returned from the POST request above
PUT http://localhost:3000/api/carts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cartItemId": 1,
  "quantity": 5
}

---

### 6. DELETE (Remove Item from Cart)
# Replace `1` with the actual cartItemId
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/carts?cartItemId=1
